<html>

<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>Thinktool, a better way to structure your thoughts.</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/landing.css">
  <link rel="icon" href="/icon.png" type="image/png">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
</head>

<body>
  <div id="top-bar">
    <span id="logo">Thinktool</span>
    <a href="/demo.html" class="demo demo-small">Demo</a>
    <a id="login-link" href="/login.html">Log in</a>
  </div>
  <main>
    <div class="block small centered">
      <h1>An associative note-taking app.</h1>

      <p>Associative note-taking is a more powerful alternative to outliners. In
        Thinktool, one note can be in multiple places. This lets you freely
        connect related notes, without needing to worry about organizing them in
        a strict hierarchy. It's a more natural way to write down your
        thoughts.</p>

      <p>
        <div class="video-embed">
          <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OOOLju8vaQU" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="block wide centered">
      <div class="horizontal features">
        <div class="feature">
          <div class="description">
            <h1>Structure.</h1>
            <p>One item can be in multiple places at once. Use this feature to
              categorize notes in the way that makes most sense, so you can
              always find the information you need.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="screenshot">
            <img src="/feature-parents.png" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <div class="description">
            <h1>Associations.</h1>
            <p>Use bidirectional links to associate related notes. With
              bidirectional links, you don't have to worry about how to
              structure your notes &ndash; just add the links, and Thinktool
              will do the rest.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="screenshot">
            <img src="/feature-links.png" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <div class="description">
            <h1>Exploration.</h1>
            <p>Thinktool automatically shows you related
              notes. Easily jump to other places where a note exists with <i>other
                parents</i>, or find out where it's mentioned with <i>references</i>.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="screenshot">
            <img src="/feature-explore.png" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="block edge newsletter-outer">
      <div class="small centered newsletter">
        <div>
          <h1>Stay updated.</h1>
          <p>Receive monthly updates about new features
            and get a look behind the scenes at Thinktool by subscribing to the
            newsletter.</p>
        </div>
        <form action="{{apiUrl}}/newsletter/subscribe" method="POST">
          <input type="email" name="email" required placeholder="you@example.com" />
          <input type="submit" value="Subcribe" />
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="block horizontal flip-900">
      <div class="box small">
        <h1>Try it.</h1>
        <p>I'm currently developing Thinktool. Therefore, it's quite
          unstable, and the current preview is mainly intended for testing.</p>
        <p>That being said, you can check it out now, and if you like it, you
          can <a href="/login.html"><span>sign up</span></a> for an account.
          The preview is currently free, but Thinktool may become a paid
          subscription service in the future. Click the button below to check
          out a free demo in your browser:</p> <a href="/demo.html" class="demo demo-big">Go to demo</a>
      </div>

      <div class="box small">
        <h1>Alternatives to Thinktool.</h1>

        <p>Thinktool is directly inspired by outliners like
          <a href="https://orgmode.org/" rel="nofollow" class="external-app-link"><span>Org mode</span></a>,
          <a href="https://workflowy.com/" rel="nofollow" class="external-app-link"><span>Workflowy</span></a> and
          <a href="https://dynalist.io/" rel="nofollow" class="external-app-link"><span>Dynalist</span></a>,
          but Thinktool uses a more powerful data model underneath.</p>

        <p><a href="https://roamresearch.com/" rel="nofollow" class="external-app-link"><span>Roam</span></a> is another
          unusual
          outliner that tries to solve the same problems as Thinktool but takes
          a different approach.</p>

        <p>Thinktool structures your data in a similar way to <a href="https://thebrain.com/"
            class="external-app-link"><span>TheBrain</span></a>, but while
          Thinktool looks like an outliner, TheBrain looks like a mind-map.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>
    Made by <a href="https://johv.dk/"><span>Jonas Hvid</span></a>. Message me at <a class="email"
      href="mailto:jonas@thinktool.io"><span>jonas@thinktool.io</span></a>.
  </footer>

  <script>fetch(`{{apiUrl}}/ping`, { mode: "no-cors" });</script>
</body>

</html>